<Requirements version="3" hierarchy="LLR">
  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.1 Explore Maze -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration State Machine</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.1.4</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RUN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RUN--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INIT--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a top-level mission control state machine with at least the states {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED} and deterministic transitions between them, such that:
(1) In the IDLE state, the state machine shall wait for receipt of an INIT_COMPLETED indication from the initialization module and then transition to EXPLORE.
(2) In the EXPLORE state, the state machine shall periodically request frontier targets from the frontier-generation module, request paths to the selected target from the path planner, and command the motion controller to execute the resulting motion primitives until either exploration completion or an exploration timeout event is received.
(3) In the RETURN_TO_START state, the state machine shall invoke the return-to-start service to compute a path to the start cell and shall command the motion controller to execute that path until the start cell is reached or a planning failure is reported.
(4) In the SECOND_RUN state, the state machine shall invoke the second-run planning service to compute the fastest path from the start cell to the goal region, shall command the motion controller to execute that path, and shall wait for receipt of a second-run status (success or failure).
(5) In the COMPLETED state, the state machine shall cease issuing new motion commands and maintain the final second-run status for external reporting.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Start Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INIT--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall cause the mission control state machine to enter the EXPLORE state automatically when, within the periodic control loop, the initialization module has signaled INIT_COMPLETED and the sensor abstraction layer has provided at least one valid set of ultrasonic and infrared measurements.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Stop Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.6</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall terminate the EXPLORE state and initiate RETURN_TO_START when either:
(1) the map completeness condition defined by the grid map module indicates that no cell or inter-cell wall segment remains in the UNKNOWN state, or
(2) the global exploration time limit defined in the time-limit requirement has been reached,
whichever condition is signaled first by the corresponding modules.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier-Based Exploration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a frontier-based exploration strategy in the EXPLORE state such that the mission control state machine selects as navigation targets cells that are currently classified as UNKNOWN but are adjacent (in the 4-neighborhood) to at least one FREE cell in the internal grid map and requests paths to these targets from the path planner.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.6">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier Generation Module</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a frontier-generation module that, upon request from the mission control state machine or planner, returns the set of all cells whose state is UNKNOWN and that are 4-neighbors of at least one FREE cell in the grid map, and shall recompute this set whenever the classification of any cell changes from UNKNOWN to FREE or BLOCKED.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Target Selection Heuristic</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall prioritize exploration frontier targets using a heuristic that:
(1) computes the estimated travel-time component using the same cell-to-cell traversal cost model defined in the path optimality criterion requirement, and
(2) adds a term that prefers frontiers expected to increase the number of newly observable cells,
and shall select targets that minimize this combined heuristic while ensuring that the estimated time to reach and explore the target does not exceed the remaining exploration time defined by the time-aware planning requirement.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.2 Wall Detection -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Front Wall Detection From Ultrasonic</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--2.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall interpret a front ultrasonic distance measurement d as a front wall in the current maze cell if the closed interval [d-12 cm, d+12 cm], derived from the ultrasonic uncertainty model, intersects the expected robot-center-to-wall distance interval for the current cell and pose that is computed from the 17.2 cm cell size and the 11 cm robot diameter.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Side Wall Detection From IR</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall interpret an active obstacle indication from a left or right infrared sensor as a wall located along the corresponding side of the current maze cell if the robot’s pose is aligned to the maze axes within a configurable angular tolerance not exceeding 10 degrees.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Proximity Thresholding</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall apply configurable numeric thresholds and hysteresis to filtered ultrasonic distance measurements to distinguish between free space and wall presence, such that single-sample noise or transient spikes do not cause flip-flopping between wall and free classifications.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Avoidance Maneuvers</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall command motor speeds to execute avoidance maneuvers (such as stopping and turning, or arc turns) when front or side wall detections indicate that the predicted robot trajectory would intersect a wall within one cell length, and shall select maneuvers that respect the robot footprint and minimum clearance margin so that collisions are prevented while maintaining progress toward exploration or path-planning goals.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.3 Create Map -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Map Data Structure</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall maintain an in-memory grid map data structure representing the 4x8 maze, where each cell and each inter-cell wall segment is explicitly stored with its classification and can be addressed by integer coordinates (row, column) aligned with the assumed physical maze geometry.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell and Wall Update From Sensors</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--POSE--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--POSE--1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall update the grid map cells and wall segments based on processed ultrasonic and infrared measurements obtained while the pose-estimation module indicates that the robot is located at a cell center or during a transition between adjacent cell centers, marking corresponding walls as PRESENT or ABSENT and updating adjacent cells as FREE if traversed without collision.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Unknown Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall initialize all cells and wall segments in the 4x8 grid map to an UNKNOWN classification at system startup prior to any sensor-based observations.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Start Cell Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall designate a fixed coordinate in the grid map as the start cell at initialization, set its classification to FREE, and maintain a record of this coordinate for use in return-to-start and second-run behaviors.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Static Map Assumption</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall treat once-observed wall and free classifications in the grid map as immutable for the duration of a mission, such that:
(1) cell states may change only from UNKNOWN to FREE or UNKNOWN to BLOCKED and shall not revert to UNKNOWN within a mission, and
(2) wall segment states may change only from UNKNOWN to PRESENT or UNKNOWN to ABSENT and shall not change between PRESENT and ABSENT or revert to UNKNOWN within a mission.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.6">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Map Completeness Criterion</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall define the map as complete when no cell and no inter-cell wall segment in the grid map remains in the UNKNOWN state, and shall provide a boolean indication of this condition to the mission control state machine.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.7">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Map Access Interface</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide a grid map access interface that offers:
(1) functions to query the classification of any cell and wall segment by (row, column) indices,
(2) functions to update the classification of cells and wall segments, and
(3) an event mechanism or callback registration by which other modules can be notified when specific cells or walls change classification,
and shall ensure that all map queries, updates, and classification-change notifications occur within the context of the periodic control loop execution so that map access is single-threaded and does not require additional synchronization.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.4 Cell Classification -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Classification Enumeration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.5</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall represent each maze cell’s state using an enumeration with at least the values {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}, shall ensure that each cell in the grid map is always in exactly one of these states, and shall allow cell state transitions only from UNKNOWN to FREE or from UNKNOWN to BLOCKED during a mission.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Segment Classification Enumeration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.5</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall represent each wall segment between adjacent cells using an enumeration with at least the values {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}, and shall allow wall segment state transitions only from UNKNOWN to PRESENT or from UNKNOWN to ABSENT during a mission, so that once a wall is classified as PRESENT or ABSENT it shall not change state or revert to UNKNOWN in that mission.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Free Cell Confirmation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall mark a cell as FREE when the robot has successfully traversed into the cell without detecting a collision or blocking wall on the entry face, and no contradictory evidence, as defined by the sensor consistency-check requirement, has been accumulated for that cell.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Blocked Cell Inference</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall mark a neighboring cell as BLOCKED if a wall segment between the current cell and that neighbor is classified as PRESENT, and shall never issue movement commands that attempt to enter a cell classified as BLOCKED.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.5 Time Constraint -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.5.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Global Mapping Time Limit</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall enforce a global time limit of 5 minutes from the start of exploration, after which it shall cease further exploration moves and signal to the mission control state machine that a timeout condition has occurred to initiate RETURN_TO_START, regardless of mapping completeness.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.5.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Time-Aware Planning</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall estimate remaining exploration time based on elapsed time and a configurable parameter representing the nominal time to traverse one cell at exploration speed, and shall avoid selecting exploration targets that cannot be reasonably reached and mapped before the 5 minute exploration time limit.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.5.3">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Nominal Cell Traversal Duration Parameter</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall maintain a configurable parameter representing the nominal time required to traverse one maze cell at exploration speed, expressed in milliseconds, and shall make this parameter available to time-aware planning and exploration modules for remaining-time estimation.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--PLAN--1.1 Path Planning -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell-Based Path Planner</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a cell-based path planning algorithm (such as Dijkstra or A*) operating on the 4x8 grid map, where nodes correspond to FREE cells and edges connect orthogonally adjacent FREE cells (4-connected grid) that are not separated by PRESENT walls.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Path Optimality Criterion</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall define path optimality as minimizing total traversal cost, where each move between orthogonally adjacent FREE cells has a non-negative cost that may be parameterized to distinguish straight-travel and turning penalties, and shall compute paths that minimize the sum of such costs between a given start and goal region.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Handling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--ENV--3.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall treat the selected 2x2 goal region as a set of up to four FREE goal cells and shall compute an optimal path from a given start cell to any of these goal cells, selecting the path with minimal traversal cost.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Replanning Capability</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.7</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall recompute planned paths whenever newly acquired map information marks previously assumed FREE cells or ABSENT walls as BLOCKED or PRESENT and the current path would otherwise traverse those blocked cells or walls, using the grid map access interface to detect invalidation events.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Planning Failure Reporting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall detect and signal a planning failure when no path exists between the current cell and the desired target or goal region in the current map, so that higher-level logic can report failure or select alternative behavior.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RUN--1.1 Return to Start -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Return Path Computation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--EVENT--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide a return-to-start service that, when invoked by the mission control state machine after receipt of either an EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event or an EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event, computes a path from the robot’s current cell to the designated start cell using the path planning algorithm and current grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Return Path Execution</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall execute the computed return path cell by cell by issuing motor speed commands that move the robot between cell centers using motion primitives, while monitoring sensors to avoid collisions and triggering replanning if the path becomes invalid due to updated map information.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RUN--1.2 Second Run and HL--RUN--1.3 Efficient Path Execution -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RUN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall initiate the SECOND_RUN state in the mission control state machine after the robot has returned to the start cell and exploration has been declared complete by the exploration module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Fastest Path Computation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--ENV--3.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall compute the fastest path from the start cell to the selected goal region using the grid map and path planner by configuring the traversal cost model parameters so that the resulting path minimizes an estimate of physical travel time during the second run.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Fast Path Motion Profile</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall execute the fastest path using motor speed commands that increase translational speed relative to exploration while limiting the commanded speeds to computed maximum permissible values that ensure the robot can safely stop before a wall given the configured sensor sampling rate, emergency-stop threshold, and ultrasonic uncertainty.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Success Criteria</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall declare the second run a success when the robot reaches any FREE cell in the 2x2 goal region following the fastest path without any detected collision; otherwise it shall declare the second run a failure.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Status Reporting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide a boolean or enumerated status output indicating success or failure of the second run upon completion or abort of the SECOND_RUN state for use by the mission control state machine and external reporting.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RELIAB--1.1 Collision Avoidance -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.1.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Minimum Wall Clearance</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--2.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall enforce a configurable minimum clearance margin M &gt; 0 cm between the robot’s circular footprint of radius 5.5 cm and any wall position derived from the grid map, where M shall be selected to cover estimated worst-case pose and wall localization errors based on the ultrasonic uncertainty model, and shall ensure that planned and executed trajectories do not violate this clearance when following ideal commands.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.1.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Emergency Stop on Imminent Collision</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall immediately command both motors to speed 0 by invoking the motor command interface if filtered sensor data indicates an obstacle or wall within a configurable emergency distance threshold shorter than the nominal stopping distance at the current speed, and shall not resume movement until a new safe trajectory has been established.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RELIAB--1.2 Sensor Noise Handling -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.2.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Sensor Sampling and Filtering</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall sample ultrasonic and infrared sensors at a configurable rate in the range [10, 50] Hz, with a default value of 20 Hz and timing jitter not exceeding a specified tolerance, and shall apply temporal filtering (such as moving average or median filters) to the sampled data to reduce the effect of random noise before using the data for wall detection or planning decisions, and shall perform this sampling once per iteration of the periodic control loop.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.2.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Consistency Checks on Sensor Data</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall compare new sensor-based wall observations against existing map entries and shall treat large, isolated discrepancies as potential sensor errors, requiring at least N configurable consecutive sensor readings that indicate a wall where the map currently stores FREE or ABSENT before changing the established wall or cell classification, where N shall be an integer greater than or equal to 2 with a documented default value of 3 and a recommended configuration range 2 ≤ N ≤ 10.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--1.1 Sensor Processing -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Sensor Abstraction Layer</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a sensor abstraction layer that wraps the ultrasonic_get_distance and infrared_get_dsl_status/infrared_get_dsr_status functions and exposes normalized sensor data structures to higher-level modules, including for each control cycle:
(1) an ultrasonic measurement represented as (distance_cm, timestamp), where distance_cm is a float in centimeters in the robot-forward frame, and
(2) infrared measurements represented as (left_flag, right_flag, timestamp), where each flag is a binary obstacle indication and timestamp is the acquisition time.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Invalid Sensor Reading Handling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall detect invalid or out-of-range sensor return values, such as negative distances or implementation-specific saturation codes, and shall ignore these readings or replace them with safe default estimates rather than using them directly for mapping or control decisions.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--1.2 Actuator Control -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Motor Command Interface</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall control the differential drive motors exclusively via the function motor_set(uint8_t left_speed, uint8_t right_speed), using integer speed values in the range [0,100] for each motor, and shall invoke motor_set at most once per iteration of the periodic control loop at the control loop frequency.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Speed Command Rate Limiting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall limit the rate of change of successive motor_set speed commands by enforcing configurable maximum increments per control cycle for left and right speeds to avoid abrupt accelerations or decelerations that could cause wheel slippage or loss of control.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--2.1, 2.2, 2.3 Ultrasonic -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--2.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Ultrasonic Distance Acquisition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, once per sensor sampling period defined by the noise-handling requirement and synchronized with the periodic control loop, call ultrasonic_get_distance() and interpret the returned float value as the distance in centimeters to the nearest front obstacle along the sensor beam in the robot-forward frame.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--2.3.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Ultrasonic Uncertainty Model</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall model each ultrasonic distance measurement as having an uncertainty interval of at least ±12 cm around the measured distance value and shall incorporate this interval into wall distance estimation, collision risk computations, and clearance-margin evaluations.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--3.x IR sensors -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--3.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Status Acquisition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, at each sensor sampling period synchronized with the periodic control loop, call infrared_get_dsl_status() and infrared_get_dsr_status() and interpret each returned uint8_t value as a binary obstacle detection flag for the respective left and right infrared sensors.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--3.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Effective Range Assumption</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall assume that a positive obstacle indication from an infrared sensor corresponds to an obstacle located approximately 4 cm from the sensor along its measurement direction and shall use this nominal distance when inferring side wall positions in the grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--3.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Orientation Compensation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall account for the approximately 25 degree mounting angle of each infrared sensor relative to the robot front direction when transforming infrared obstacle detections into equivalent lateral wall distances and positions in the maze reference frame.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--HARDWARE--1.1 Robot Shape -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Robot Footprint Model</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall model the robot as a circle of radius 5.5 cm when checking for possible collisions with walls located at cell boundaries spaced approximately 17.2 cm apart and when evaluating clearance against the minimum clearance margin.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--HARDWARE--2.1 Differential Drive -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Differential Drive Kinematics</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement kinematic equations for a differential drive robot to estimate changes in robot orientation and position over time based on the left and right motor speed commands and the control-loop period T or measured cycle duration from the scheduling module, without assuming constant rotational speed.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell-Center Motion Primitives</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide motion primitives that move the robot from one maze cell center to an adjacent cell center and turn in place to discrete headings aligned with maze axes, using sequences of motor_set commands whose durations and speeds are derived from the differential-drive kinematics and cell dimension of approximately 17.2 cm.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--HARDWARE--2.3 Translational Velocity -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Speed Limitation for Safety</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--2.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall constrain the commanded motor speeds such that the resulting translational speed does not exceed a configured maximum below the 200 cm/s hardware capability, where this maximum speed is computed to ensure that, given the configured sensor sampling rate, emergency-stop distance threshold, and ultrasonic uncertainty, the robot can safely stop before reaching a detected wall.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--ENV--1.x Maze properties -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Coordinate System</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall define a grid coordinate system with 4 rows and 8 columns for the maze, with a consistent convention for mapping physical positions to cell indices, such as defining row 0, column 0 as the start cell, and shall use this convention consistently across mapping, planning, and control modules.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Geometry Parameters</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall use the approximate cell dimension of 17.2 cm when transforming between estimated traveled distances and transitions between maze cell centers for pose estimation, motion primitive generation, and grid map updates.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Geometry Parameters</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall use an approximate wall thickness of 1.6 cm when reasoning about the physical extent of walls relative to the robot footprint in collision and clearance checks.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Inter-Cell Wall Indexing</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall index possible wall positions as boundaries between horizontally and vertically adjacent cells and shall store wall presence or absence for each such boundary in the grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--3.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Identification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, upon completion of exploration, identify as candidate goal regions all contiguous 2x2 blocks of cells that are all classified as FREE and reachable from the start cell in the grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--3.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Selection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, when multiple candidate 2x2 FREE regions exist, select as the maze goal region the one that minimizes the optimal path cost from the start cell according to the traversal cost metric defined for the path planner, and shall provide this selected region to the second-run planning module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- Additional LLRs -->

  <Requirement ID="LL--POSE--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell-Level Pose Estimation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall maintain an estimate of the robot’s current maze cell index (row, column) and discrete heading aligned with the maze axes, updated in each control loop cycle by integrating the differential drive kinematics over the control-loop period T or measured cycle duration provided by the scheduling module and the issued motor speed commands.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--POSE--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Pose Correction Using Map Features</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.2.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall correct accumulated orientation and position error in the pose estimate when the robot is aligned with maze axes and wall detections indicate proximity to known cell boundaries, by snapping the estimated heading to the nearest axis-aligned direction and adjusting the position to the nearest cell center consistent with the wall observations.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--POSE--1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Center Entry Notification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--POSE--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall detect when the pose estimate crosses from one cell center to an adjacent cell center and shall notify the mapping module of the new current cell index so that cell and wall updates can be associated with the correct cell transition.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--EVENT--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Status Events</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.6</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement an exploration-status module, integrated with the mission control state machine, that publishes EXPLORATION_COMPLETED and EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT events by enqueuing corresponding event records into a system event queue accessible to the mission control and return-to-start modules when, respectively, the map completeness criterion indicates a complete map or the global exploration time limit is reached.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--SCHED--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Periodic Control Loop Scheduling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a periodic control loop with a configurable period T such that the control loop frequency equals the sensor sampling rate defined in the sensor sampling requirement, and in each cycle it shall:
(1) acquire sensor readings via the sensor abstraction layer,
(2) update the grid map using the mapping module,
(3) update the mission control state machine,
(4) compute or update the current path as required by the active state, and
(5) issue motor_set commands via the motion control module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INIT--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Initialization Completion Signaling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement an initialization module that, after all required hardware and software initialization routines have successfully completed, sets an INIT_COMPLETED flag or publishes an INIT_COMPLETED event within the main execution context, and the mission control state machine shall only transition from IDLE to EXPLORE after this indication is present.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>
</Requirements>
<Design>
    <Components version="1">
        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--1</ID>
            <Name>Mission Control State Machine</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Central mission coordinator that implements the top-level mission control state machine with states {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED}. It drives exploration, triggers return-to-start and second-run behaviors, selects exploration targets using a frontier-based heuristic, monitors exploration status and time limits, and commands motion execution through the motion control module. It owns the mission state, remaining-time estimation for exploration, and the final second-run status presented to external reporting.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--2</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_CurrentState</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Enumerated current mission state {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED}. Updated every control loop cycle after mission state update. Used by dependent modules (exploration-status, motion control, return-to-start, second-run) to gate their behavior.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExploreTargetRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Request sent in EXPLORE state to Frontier Generation Module for a set of current frontier cells. Contains current robot cell (row, col) and current map version/cycle index. Issued at most once per control loop when exploration target selection logic needs new frontiers.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SecondRunStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Enumerated status {NOT_STARTED, RUNNING, SUCCESS, FAILURE}. Updated when SECOND_RUN is active and upon completion/abort. COMPLETED state latches the last non-RUNNING value for external reporting.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ActivePathGoal</Name>
                            <Description>
                                For RETURN_TO_START and SECOND_RUN, indicates current goal (either start cell or selected goal region target cell). Includes goal cell coordinates and mission phase.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExplorationPhaseControl</Name>
                            <Description>
                                High-level phase indication for motion controller: {EXPLORATION_MOTION, RETURN_MOTION, SECOND_RUN_MOTION, STOPPED}. Used to select proper speed profiles and planning modes.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExploreTargetSelection</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Motion Planning & Target Selection (CMP--2) back to Mission Control: selected exploration target cell (row, col) and associated path feasibility/estimated cost. Mission control uses this to instruct motion controller to follow the planned path.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Motion Planning & Target Selection: indicates {IDLE, PATH_EXECUTING, PATH_REACHED, PATH_FAILED}. Used to determine when to request new frontier targets, when to switch states (e.g., after reaching start cell in RETURN_TO_START) or to handle planning failures.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SecondRunPathStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Motion Planning & Target Selection / Motion Controller: indicates completion or failure of the second-run fastest path execution; includes collision-free flag.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MissionMode</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Mission mode broadcast to Mapping & Grid Map module: indicates when exploration is active and when exploration is complete, so grid map can lock goal-region selection when requested.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MapCompleteFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean indication from Mapping & Grid Map that the map completeness criterion is satisfied (no UNKNOWN cells or wall segments) according to LL--MAP--1.3.6. Sampled every control loop cycle to decide exploration termination.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_FrontierSet</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Frontier Generation (part of CMP--3 or CMP--2 depending on implementation choice): the current list/vector of frontier cells (row, col) that meet the UNKNOWN + 4-neighbor FREE definition. Mission control passes this into CMP--2 for heuristic-based selection.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExploreActive</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean: true when mission state is EXPLORE. Provided to Exploration Status & Time-Limit module to start/stop its timers and event generation.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExplorationCompletedEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Event record representing EXPLORATION_COMPLETED, enqueued by Exploration Status module when map completeness is achieved before timeout. Consumed by mission control in EXPLORE to initiate transition to RETURN_TO_START.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExplorationTimeoutEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Event record representing EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT after the 5-minute limit is exceeded. Also triggers transition from EXPLORE to RETURN_TO_START.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--5</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ReturnToStartInvoke</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Command signal to Return-to-Start & Second-Run module indicating that RETURN_TO_START state has been entered and a return path must be computed using current pose and start cell.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SecondRunInvoke</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Command signal that SECOND_RUN state has been entered and that fastest path computation plus motion execution should be started.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ReturnPathReached</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean or event from CMP--5 indicating that the robot has reached the start cell following the return path. Used to trigger transition IDLE? or SECOND_RUN depending on exploration completion status (per LL--RUN--1.2.1).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SecondRunResult</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Enumerated result {SUCCESS, FAILURE}. Mission control records this and transitions to COMPLETED, exposing the final status externally.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--6</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_InitStatusRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Implicit polling/reading of INIT_COMPLETED indication from Initialization module performed at each control loop cycle while in IDLE. Not an active message, but a logical dependency.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_InitCompletedFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean or event flag set by Initialization module indicating that all hardware and software initialization is complete. Mission control uses this to trigger IDLE -&gt; EXPLORE.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionEnable</Name>
                            <Description>
                                High-level enable/disable to Motion Control & Collision Avoidance: false in IDLE and COMPLETED, true in EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN. When false, Motion Control must command zero speed.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionGoalPath</Name>
                            <Description>
                                For each phase, the intended path (sequence of cell centers) plus associated motion profile type {EXPLORATION, RETURN, FAST_SECOND_RUN}. Sourced from CMP--2 / CMP--5 and passed-through so Motion Control can execute with correct profile.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionPhaseComplete</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notification from Motion Control when all path segments for the current mission phase have been executed or when motion has been stopped due to emergency stop. Used alongside planner feedback to determine transitions.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--8</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExternalMissionStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Summary mission status for external reporting: current mission state, exploration completion flag, second run status, and reason for termination (map complete, timeout, collision, planning failure). Generated in COMPLETED state and updated on changes.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExternalStartCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional external trigger to start initialization or exploration. If present, Mission Control will require both INIT_COMPLETED and this start command before leaving IDLE; otherwise only INIT_COMPLETED is required. Not directly mandated by LLRs but provided for extensibility.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--9</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_RemainingExplorationTime</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Remaining exploration time (ms) broadcast to Time-Aware Planning and Target Selection module every control loop during EXPLORE. Computed as max(0, 5min - elapsed_exploration_time).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ElapsedTimeUpdate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Control Loop Scheduler / Time service: current mission elapsed time since start, and exploration-phase elapsed time. Used to compute remaining time and to detect global timeout.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SensorReadyForExplore</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Derived flag indicating that at least one valid combined ultrasonic + IR measurement set is available in current cycle. Used with INIT_COMPLETED to satisfy LL--MAP--1.1.2 exploration start condition.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SensorValidity</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Sensor Abstraction Layer: indicates whether the latest ultrasonic and IR readings are valid and not out-of-range; includes timestamps so Mission Control ensures data freshness at EXPLORE entry.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Executed once per iteration of the periodic control loop (CMP--9) after sensor and map updates and before motion commands. The component maintains internal mission state variables and reacts to external events (INIT_COMPLETED, exploration status events, planning status, motion completion, pose updates).

                Transition conditions:
                - IDLE is the initial state upon power-up. In IDLE, motor commands are disabled and no paths are planned.
                - Transition IDLE -&gt; EXPLORE occurs when:
                    * Initialization module indicates INIT_COMPLETED (flag true or event present), and
                    * Sensor abstraction layer has produced at least one valid combined ultrasonic + IR measurement within the last control cycle, and
                    * No blocking fault state is present.
                - In EXPLORE, each cycle Mission Control:
                    * Requests/upkeeps frontier list via CMP--3 / CMP--2.
                    * Asks planner for a path to the currently selected frontier.
                    * Commands motion along the current path if available.
                    * Monitors exploration status events (EXPLORATION_COMPLETED, EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT).
                    * On EXPLORATION_COMPLETED or EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT, stops issuing new exploration targets, commands motion stop for exploration paths, then transitions to RETURN_TO_START.
                - In RETURN_TO_START, Mission Control:
                    * Invokes return-to-start service once on entry.
                    * Monitors path status/pose to detect arrival at start cell or planning failure.
                    * On reaching start cell with a valid path and if exploration had completed successfully, transitions to SECOND_RUN.
                    * If exploration has not been completed (timeout or planning failure), returns to COMPLETED or a terminal failure state, without second run.
                - In SECOND_RUN, Mission Control:
                    * Invokes fastest-path computation to goal region once on entry.
                    * Enables fast-motion profile (CMP--7).
                    * Monitors second-run result and collision/emergency stop signals.
                    * On path completion without collision and goal reached, records SUCCESS.
                    * On planning failure, collision, or inability to reach any goal cell, records FAILURE.
                    * In either case, transitions to COMPLETED.
                - In COMPLETED, Mission Control:
                    * Commands standstill (no new motion).
                    * Latches final second-run status and exploration completion/timeout cause.
                    * Does not leave COMPLETED without a system reset (not specified in LLRs).
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Updated once per periodic control loop iteration as required by LL--SCHED--1.1.1.
                - Assumes control loop frequency equals sensor sampling frequency (10–50 Hz, default 20 Hz).
                - Time-based decisions (5-minute exploration timeout, remaining exploration time) are computed using timestamps provided by scheduler/time services, not by counting cycles alone, to respect jitter tolerance.
                - State transitions are deterministic: for each combination of current state and input events in a given cycle, at most one transition is taken; conflicting events are resolved with priority rules:
                    * In EXPLORE: EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT takes precedence over EXPLORATION_COMPLETED if both appear in same cycle; both lead to RETURN_TO_START but timeout is recorded as cause.
                    * In SECOND_RUN: emergency stop / collision events take precedence over success; if goal reached and collision simultaneously reported, second run is considered FAILURE.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Mission state is always one of {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED}.
                - State transitions are acyclic except for self-loops within a state; there is no transition that re-enters IDLE from any other state.
                - While in IDLE or COMPLETED, no non-zero motion commands are permitted (Motion Control must be disabled).
                - While in EXPLORE:
                    * Only exploration-target-based paths are requested.
                    * Return-to-start and second-run services are not invoked.
                - While in RETURN_TO_START:
                    * Exploration-target selection is disabled.
                    * Only start cell is used as goal for planning.
                - While in SECOND_RUN:
                    * Only fastest-path-to-goal-region planning is active.
                    * Exploration or return planning are not re-invoked.
                - The second-run final status is immutable after entering COMPLETED until system reset.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                Potential failure states and handling:
                - Planning failure in EXPLORE (no path to any frontier):
                    * Path planner (CMP--2) reports PATH_FAILED for all candidate frontier targets.
                    * Mission Control records exploration as terminated due to planning failure; it still initiates RETURN_TO_START using the best-known map.
                - Planning failure in RETURN_TO_START:
                    * Return-to-start service reports inability to find path to start cell.
                    * Mission Control records a mission failure cause; it transitions directly to COMPLETED with MC_SecondRunStatus set to FAILURE, skipping SECOND_RUN.
                - Planning failure in SECOND_RUN:
                    * Fastest path cannot be found to any FREE goal-cell in selected goal region.
                    * Mission Control sets second run status to FAILURE and transitions to COMPLETED.
                - Emergency stop in any motion state (EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN):
                    * Motion Control raises emergency-stop event.
                    * Mission Control halts further planning requests for the current phase.
                    * In EXPLORE: may trigger replanning; if repeated or unrecoverable, triggers forced exploration termination and RETURN_TO_START.
                    * In RETURN_TO_START or SECOND_RUN: considered mission failure, triggers transition to COMPLETED or reverts to safe stop policy.
                - Missing or invalid INIT_COMPLETED:
                    * If INIT_COMPLETED is never asserted, mission remains in IDLE indefinitely, no exploration occurs.
                - Sensor data never valid:
                    * Exploration cannot start because exploration start condition requires at least one valid sensor set; mission remains in IDLE.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.1; LL--MAP--1.1.2; LL--MAP--1.1.3; LL--MAP--1.1.4; LL--MAP--1.1.5; LL--MAP--1.5.1; LL--MAP--1.5.2; LL--RUN--1.1.1; LL--RUN--1.2.1; LL--RUN--1.2.2; LL--RUN--1.2.3; LL--RUN--1.2.4; LL--RUN--1.2.5; LL--EVENT--1.1.1; LL--SCHED--1.1.1; LL--INIT--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--2</ID>
            <Name>Motion Planning & Target Selection</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Provides frontier-based exploration target selection and cell-based path planning services for all mission phases. Implements the cell-based planner (e.g., A*), path-cost model, goal-region handling, replanning on map updates, and planning failure reporting. For exploration, it uses a heuristic that combines travel-time estimates with an information gain term, while respecting remaining exploration time. It exposes planned paths to Motion Control and status back to Mission Control.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_MapQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Requests to read cell and wall classifications, including FREE/BLOCKED and wall states, via the grid map access interface. Used in graph construction and heuristic estimation.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_MapUpdateRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Requests to update classification of specific cells/walls (e.g., mark neighbor BLOCKED when PRESENT wall detected). These are typically invoked by mapping logic but may be required by planner-driven inference steps.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_MapData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Responses to map queries (cell and wall enumerations) and asynchronous notifications of classification changes (callbacks) per LL--MAP--1.3.7. Includes which cells/walls changed and from what to what state.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_FrontierSet</Name>
                            <Description>
                                List of frontier cells computed by Frontier Generation module (part of CMP--3). Each entry includes (row, col) and optionally an estimate of frontier size (number of neighboring UNKNOWN cells) to help in heuristic estimation.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_MapCompleteFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean indicating map completeness, used to determine whether exploration planning is still required.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_ExploreTargetSelection</Name>
                            <Description>
                                For EXPLORE state: selected frontier cell that minimizes combined heuristic subject to remaining time constraints. Returned after processing frontier set and computing estimated traversal time and expected information gain per candidate.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_PathStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Current planning and path-execution status: {IDLE, PATH_AVAILABLE, PATH_EXECUTING, PATH_REACHED, PATH_FAILED}. Updated as Motion Control advances along planned path and as replanning occurs.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_SecondRunPathStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Same as PL_PathStatus but dedicated to SECOND_RUN fastest path. Indicates completion of second run and path validity state.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_ExploreFrontierRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Mission Control: request to select next exploration target, containing frontier set reference and remaining exploration time.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_ReturnToStartRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Mission Control or Return-to-Start module: request to compute path from current cell to start cell.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_SecondRunPlanningRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Mission Control / Return-to-Start module: request to compute fastest path from start cell to selected 2x2 goal region.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_PlannedPath</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Planned path as an ordered list of cell centers: [c0 = start, c1, ..., cn = goal]. For each edge (ci, ci+1) includes turn requirement and estimated traversal cost, enabling Motion Control to choose appropriate motion primitives.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_ExecutionHints</Name>
                            <Description>
                                For each segment: motion profile hints such as preferred speed (normalized 0–100), straight/turn classification, and any time constraints. Derived from traversal cost model and mission phase (exploration vs second run).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_PathExecutionFeedback</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Motion Control: index of last reached cell in path, collision flags, and whether planned path remains feasible (no emergency stops). Used to detect PATH_REACHED or PATH_FAILED and to trigger replanning if map invalidation or emergency stops occur.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--9</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_TimeAwareParameters</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Additional time-aware planning parameters (e.g., estimated per-cell traversal times) computed from nominal cell traversal duration; used by planner heuristics.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_RemainingExplorationTime</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Remaining exploration time in ms, provided by Mission Control/time module, used by planner when deciding whether an exploration target is admissible under LL--MAP--1.5.2.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Invoked in each control loop iteration (after map update) to:
                    * Check for pending planning requests (exploration target selection, return-to-start, second run).
                    * Process map change notifications to determine if active paths are invalid.
                    * Update internal A* (or Dijkstra) search structures as needed.
                    * Provide path segments and planning status to Motion Control and Mission Control.

                Cell-based Planner:
                - Represents the maze as a 4x8 grid with nodes equal to FREE cells (LL--PLAN--1.1.1) as reported via CMP--3.
                - Constructs a 4-connected adjacency graph:
                    * For each FREE cell (r, c), neighbors are at (r±1, c) and (r, c±1) when within bounds, both cells FREE, and the wall segment between them is not PRESENT (must be ABSENT or UNKNOWN).
                    * Edges store:
                        - Straight movement indicator (same heading as current approach) or turn requirement.
                        - Traversal cost computed from Path Optimality Criterion (LL--PLAN--1.1.2).
                - Path Optimality:
                    * Each edge cost = base_straight_cost or (straight_cost + turn_penalty) depending on heading change.
                    * Cost model parameters (straight_cost, turn_penalty) are configurable and may be re-parameterized for second run to approximate physical travel time.
                    * Planner computes minimal sum of edge costs from start cell to:
                        - frontier target (~single cell),
                        - start cell (return),
                        - any goal cell in a 2x2 goal region.

                Exploration Target Selection (Frontier-Based):
                - Receives the current frontier set: all UNKNOWN cells with at least one FREE 4-neighbor (LL--MAP--1.1.6).
                - For each frontier cell f:
                    * Computes shortest path cost from current cell to a reachable FREE neighbor of f (since f itself is UNKNOWN and unlikely to be directly traversable yet). Path uses the same cost model as planner (LL--MAP--1.1.5(1)).
                    * Estimates travel time component = path_cost * time_per_cost_unit (derived from nominal cell traversal duration).
                    * Estimates expected information gain:
                        - For each frontier, counts the number of adjacent UNKNOWN cells or wall segments likely to be observed upon arrival, using grid map occupancy and sensor geometry.
                        - Derives an information-gain score IG(f).
                    * Combined heuristic H(f) = alpha * travel_time_estimate - beta * IG(f), where alpha, beta &gt;= 0 are tunable weights (prefer lower H).
                    * Applies time-awareness: if travel_time_estimate + expected time to scan frontier (e.g., k * nominal_cell_traversal_time) &gt; remaining exploration time, the frontier is discarded as infeasible (LL--MAP--1.5.2).
                - Selects frontier with minimal H(f) subject to feasibility. If multiple frontiers tie, choose one with:
                    * Smaller travel time, then
                    * Larger information gain.
                - If no feasible frontier remains:
                    * Reports exploration planning failure to Mission Control; exploration can be considered complete or aborted.

                Replanning:
                - Registers for map change notifications via CMP--3’s event callbacks (LL--PLAN--1.1.4).
                - If a cell or wall belonging to the current path is updated to BLOCKED or PRESENT (or cell changes to BLOCKED):
                    * Marks the current path as invalid.
                    * Immediately recomputes a new path with same start and goal if possible.
                    * If no valid path exists, sets PATH_FAILED and reports planning failure (LL--PLAN--1.1.5).

                Goal Region Handling:
                - When provided with a goal region (up to four FREE cells):
                    * Treats goal cells as separate goals; runs either:
                        - multi-goal Dijkstra/A*, or
                        - repeated single-goal planning to each goal cell.
                    * Selects the path with minimal traversal cost and returns that path to Motion Control (LL--PLAN--1.1.3).

                Fastest-Path (Second Run):
                - On SECOND_RUN planning request:
                    * Uses the same cell graph but re-parameterizes cost model to approximate travel time:
                        - straight moves cost proportional to physical distance / desired fast speed.
                        - turns include acceleration/deceleration penalties.
                    * Integrates any additional constraints (e.g., prefer fewer turns).
                    * Path returned is the one minimizing estimated physical travel time from start cell to chosen goal region (LL--RUN--1.2.2).

                Planning Failure Reporting:
                - If after graph expansion no path exists between current cell and target (frontier, start, goal region), sets a planning result code:
                    * NO_PATH_AVAILABLE or GOAL_UNREACHABLE.
                - Returns this status to Mission Control and/or Return-to-Start / Second-Run module (LL--PLAN--1.1.5).
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Planner may be called every control loop cycle but must complete within T (control loop period).
                - For small 4x8 grid, a full A*/Dijkstra run is well within 20–100 ms; nonetheless:
                    * Exploration target selection may be rate-limited to every N cycles (configurable) to reduce CPU load.
                    * Replanning is triggered immediately upon map invalidation events and processed in the next cycle.
                - Time-aware heuristic uses precise timestamps for remaining time comparison, not cycle counts, keeping consistent with LL--MAP--1.5.2 and LL--MAP--1.5.3.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Planner graph always respects:
                    * Only FREE cells are traversable nodes.
                    * No edge crosses a PRESENT wall segment.
                - Path cost is non-negative for any edge.
                - Current planned path (if any) always starts at the actual current cell (or nearest reachable cell) and ends at the specified goal.
                - While exploring:
                    * Selected targets are always frontier cells as defined (UNKNOWN with FREE 4-neighbor).
                    * Selected targets never violate remaining-time constraint.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Inconsistent map (e.g., start or current cell not FREE):
                    * Planner reports planning failure and refrains from returning a path.
                - Frontier set empty while time remains:
                    * Planner indicates no exploration target (may signal map complete condition mismatch).
                - Computational failure (e.g., out-of-memory for open/closed sets):
                    * For small grid this is unlikely; if it occurs, planner reports generic planning failure.
                - Replanning loop:
                    * Rapid oscillation in map invalidation and replanning is mitigated by ignoring short-lived inconsistent states (e.g., require stable BLOCKED/PRESENT classification per LL--RELIAB--1.2.2 before treating cell/wall as blocked).
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.4; LL--MAP--1.1.5; LL--MAP--1.1.6; LL--MAP--1.3.1; LL--MAP--1.3.5; LL--MAP--1.3.6; LL--MAP--1.3.7; LL--MAP--1.4.1; LL--MAP--1.4.2; LL--MAP--1.4.4; LL--MAP--1.5.2; LL--MAP--1.5.3; LL--PLAN--1.1.1; LL--PLAN--1.1.2; LL--PLAN--1.1.3; LL--PLAN--1.1.4; LL--PLAN--1.1.5; LL--RUN--1.1.1; LL--RUN--1.2.2; LL--ENV--3.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--3</ID>
            <Name>Mapping & Grid Map</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Maintains and updates the in-memory 4x8 grid map of maze cells and inter-cell walls. It initializes map states, applies sensor-based updates and classification rules, enforces static map assumptions and enumerations, computes map completeness, identifies goal-region candidates, and provides synchronous query/update and asynchronous notification APIs to other modules.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--8</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_GridVisualizationData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional export of current grid map for external monitoring: classification of each cell and wall, start cell, selected goal region. For debugging or external reporting.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_ConfigParameters</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configuration parameters such as map initialization mode, static map enforcement flags, and debug options, provided at startup by configuration subsystem.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--9</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_UpdateFromSensorsRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Trigger from Control Loop Scheduler each cycle indicating new sensor data is available; Mapping component should integrate sensors and pose to update cells and walls accordingly.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_PoseEstimate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Cell-level pose estimate (row, col, heading) plus cell-center transition events from Pose Estimation (CMP--11). Used to attribute observations to correct cells and wall boundaries.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_SensorDetections</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Processed wall detection flags and distance estimates from Wall Detection (CMP--4); includes front wall presence, side walls, and proximity thresholds results.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--2</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_AccessAPI</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Conceptual interface exposing:
                                - getCellState(row, col): returns {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}
                                - getWallState(boundary): returns {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}
                                - setCellState(row, col, newState)
                                - setWallState(boundary, newState)
                                - registerMapChangeCallback(callback)
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_ChangeNotifications</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Event-style notifications invoked whenever a cell or wall changes classification: includes coordinates, old state, new state. Single-threaded within control loop (LL--MAP--1.3.7).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_QueryRequests</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Aggregate of map queries made by planning, mission control, and other modules in the current control cycle.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_UpdateRequests</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Programmatic updates requested by other modules (e.g., blocked cell inference).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_MapCompleteFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean computed each cycle indicating map completeness (no UNKNOWN cell or wall). Provided to Mission Control and Exploration Status modules (LL--MAP--1.3.6).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_StartCellInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Start cell coordinate (row, col) and classification (FREE), maintained throughout mission (LL--MAP--1.3.4).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_GoalRegionList</Name>
                            <Description>
                                List of candidate 2x2 goal regions identified upon exploration completion: each includes the four cells and their reachability from start.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_MissionMode</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Mission mode from Mission Control indicating whether exploration is ongoing, to permit/disallow certain map modifications (e.g., static map assumption only during active mission).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_WallClassificationRequests</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Requests to update specific wall segments based on wall detection; includes boundary index and desired state {PRESENT, ABSENT}.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MAP_WallGeometryParams</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Parameters used by Wall Detection when mapping sensor readings to cell boundaries (cell size, wall thickness, robot radius).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Initialization:
                - On system startup and before any sensor observations:
                    * Define grid coordinate system with 4 rows and 8 columns (LL--ENV--1.1.1).
                    * Create in-memory arrays:
                        - cells[4][8]: each cell has classification enum {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED} (LL--MAP--1.4.1).
                        - horizontalWalls[5][8]: horizontal boundaries (between rows).
                        - verticalWalls[4][9]: vertical boundaries (between columns).
                          Each wall element has classification enum {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT} (LL--MAP--1.4.2, LL--ENV--1.4.1).
                    * Initialize all cells and walls to UNKNOWN (LL--MAP--1.3.3).
                    * Designate a fixed start cell index, e.g. (row=0, col=0), set its state to FREE, and store as startCell (LL--MAP--1.3.4).
                    * Initialize map completeness flag to false.

                Map Update per Control Loop:
                - During each loop iteration, when new pose and sensor information is available:
                    * Determine if robot is:
                        - At cell center, or
                        - Transitioning between adjacent centers (via CMP--11).
                    * If at or near cell center:
                        - Use processed wall detections (front, left, right) to:
                            + Map sensor detections to corresponding inter-cell wall indices (using cell geometry 17.2 cm, robot radius 5.5 cm, wall thickness 1.6 cm, IR distance 4 cm, and IR mounting angle 25°).
                            + For each wall segment with reliable detection:
                                · Apply static map assumption: if wall state currently UNKNOWN, update to PRESENT or ABSENT. If already PRESENT/ABSENT, do not change (LL--MAP--1.3.5).
                        - If robot has just traversed into a new cell (pose transition event):
                            + Mark this cell as FREE if:
                                · Transition occurred without collision or emergency stop on entry face.
                                · No contradictory evidence as defined by sensor consistency checks (requires N consecutive consistent readings, LL--MAP--1.4.3 and LL--RELIAB--1.2.2).
                            + For each neighboring cell where an inter-cell wall is PRESENT:
                                · Mark that neighboring cell as BLOCKED (if currently UNKNOWN) and never issue move commands into it (LL--MAP--1.4.4).
                    * When robot traverses from one cell to another without collision and with wall on entry boundary observed as ABSENT or UNKNOWN, mark both cells as FREE as appropriate.

                Completeness Criterion:
                - After each classification update:
                    * Iterate over all cells and walls to check if any remain UNKNOWN.
                    * If no UNKNOWN entries remain:
                        - Set mapComplete = true and signal via MAP_MapCompleteFlag.
                    * Else:
                        - mapComplete = false.
                - Provide map completeness boolean to Exploration Status (CMP--4) and Mission Control.

                Grid Map Access Interface:
                - Provide functions within the single-threaded control loop:
                    * CellState getCellState(row, col)
                    * void setCellState(row, col, CellState newState)
                    * WallState getWallState(boundaryIndex)
                    * void setWallState(boundaryIndex, WallState newState)
                    * void registerMapChangeCallback(callback)
                - All queries, updates, and callback invocations occur within control loop context (LL--MAP--1.3.7), so no extra synchronization is needed.

                Goal Region Identification:
                - When map is declared complete:
                    * Iterate over all contiguous 2x2 cell blocks:
                        - For each top-left coordinate (r, c) where r &lt;= 2, c &lt;= 6:
                            · Check that all four cells are FREE.
                            · Check reachability from start cell via path planner (or BFS using map graph).
                        - If reachable, add to candidate goal region list (LL--ENV--3.1.1).
                    * Provide candidate regions to Goal Region Selection logic (CMP--2/CMP--5).
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - All operations are executed within the periodic control loop (LL--SCHED--1.1.1).
                - Map update must complete before planner and mission state machine are updated in each cycle.
                - Heavy operations (completeness check, candidate goal-region search) can be amortized:
                    * Completeness check: maintain counters of UNKNOWN cells and walls, updated on each classification change rather than scanning entire map every time.
                    * Goal-region identification: executed only when mapComplete transitions from false to true.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Each cell is always in exactly one of {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}.
                - Each wall segment is always in exactly one of {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}.
                - During a mission (from initialization to mission end):
                    * Cell transitions only allowed: UNKNOWN -&gt; FREE or UNKNOWN -&gt; BLOCKED.
                    * Wall transitions only allowed: UNKNOWN -&gt; PRESENT or UNKNOWN -&gt; ABSENT.
                    * States never revert to UNKNOWN or switch between FREE and BLOCKED or between PRESENT and ABSENT (LL--MAP--1.3.5).
                - Start cell remains FREE for the entire mission.
                - Map completeness flag is true iff no cell or wall is UNKNOWN.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Inconsistent indexing:
                    * Requests for cells/walls outside 4x8 bounds are rejected with error status and ignored.
                - Violations of static map assumption (e.g., external code attempts to change an already non-UNKNOWN state):
                    * Mapping rejects the update and raises a debug assertion/log entry.
                - Conflicting sensor evidence:
                    * If new sensor readings strongly contradict established map entries, changes are subject to consistency check logic:
                        - Require N consecutive contradictory readings before any update from FREE/ABSENT to BLOCKED/PRESENT is even considered; however, static map assumption disallows reverting established states, so contradictory evidence remains flagged as potential sensor error but does not change map.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.2.1; LL--MAP--1.2.2; LL--MAP--1.3.1; LL--MAP--1.3.2; LL--MAP--1.3.3; LL--MAP--1.3.4; LL--MAP--1.3.5; LL--MAP--1.3.6; LL--MAP--1.3.7; LL--MAP--1.4.1; LL--MAP--1.4.2; LL--MAP--1.4.3; LL--MAP--1.4.4; LL--ENV--1.1.1; LL--ENV--1.2.1; LL--ENV--1.3.1; LL--ENV--1.4.1; LL--ENV--3.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--4</ID>
            <Name>Wall Detection & Avoidance</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Implements wall detection from ultrasonic and infrared sensors, performs proximity thresholding and hysteresis, and commands avoidance maneuvers and emergency stops as needed. It uses sensor abstraction data and pose alignment to infer front and side walls, feed mapping, and protect against imminent collisions while preserving mission goals.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_WallDetections</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Processed wall detection results per cycle:
                                - frontWallPresent (bool)
                                - leftWallPresent (bool)
                                - rightWallPresent (bool)
                                - estimated front distance interval [d_min, d_max]
                                - IR-based side obstacle flags.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_FilteredSensorData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Sensor Abstraction: filtered ultrasonic distance with timestamp, binary IR flags, and validity indicators.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_MapUpdateRequests</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Requests to Mapping module to set specific wall segments to PRESENT or ABSENT in grid map based on robust wall detections and pose location (LL--MAP--1.2.1, LL--MAP--1.2.2).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_CellAndWallGeometry</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Map geometry and robot footprint parameters needed to project sensor detections to grid walls: cell size 17.2 cm, robot radius 5.5 cm, wall thickness 1.6 cm.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_AvoidanceCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                High-level commands to Motion Control when predicted trajectory intersects a wall within one cell length such as:
                                - STOP_AND_TURN_LEFT
                                - STOP_AND_TURN_RIGHT
                                - ARC_TURN_LEFT/RIGHT
                                - SHORT_BRAKE
                                Each includes direction and qualitative magnitude so Motion Control can map to motor_set sequences.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_EmergencyStop</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Hard-stop request when obstacle detected closer than emergency threshold: forces Motion Control to issue immediate motor_set(0,0) and block further motion until cleared.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_PlannedTrajectory</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Approximation of near-term trajectory (e.g., next cell transitions and predicted front distance over time) used to check collision risk vs wall detections.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--11</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_PoseAlignmentUsed</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Pose alignment info (alignedWithAxes flag) used to gate IR-based side-wall decisions (LL--MAP--1.2.2).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_CurrentPose</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Pose estimate (cell, heading, alignment error) from Pose Estimation. Used to compute expected robot-center-to-wall distances and to convert sensor beams into map-frame distances.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Wall Detection Logic:

                Front Wall from Ultrasonic (LL--MAP--1.2.1, LL--INTERF--2.3.1):
                - On each sensor sample (once per control loop cycle):
                    * Obtain filtered ultrasonic distance d (cm) from sensor abstraction.
                    * Model measurement as interval [d-12, d+12] cm based on ultrasonic uncertainty (LL--INTERF--2.3.1).
                    * Compute expected robot-center-to-wall distance interval [d_exp_min, d_exp_max] for current cell and pose:
                        - Use cell dimension 17.2 cm, robot radius 5.5 cm, and wall thickness 1.6 cm to determine expected nominal distance from robot center at cell center to front wall.
                        - Expand by pose estimation error margin.
                    * If [d-12, d+12] intersects [d_exp_min, d_exp_max], classify front wall PRESENT in the corresponding boundary of the current cell; else, classify ABSENT if consistently non-intersecting over N consecutive cycles (respecting static map rules).

                Side Wall from IR (LL--MAP--1.2.2, LL--INTERF--3.1.1, 3.3.1, 3.4.1):
                - On each sensor sample:
                    * Acquire left_flag and right_flag from IR sensors.
                    * Determine if robot pose is aligned to maze axes within configured tolerance (≤ 10°):
                        - If not aligned, ignore IR flags for mapping decisions this cycle.
                    * If aligned and left_flag is active:
                        - Model a wall at approximately 4 cm along left sensor beam (LL--INTERF--3.3.1).
                        - Apply 25° mounting angle to map detection to lateral distance and position relative to cell boundaries (LL--INTERF--3.4.1).
                        - Identify corresponding left-side wall segment between current cell and adjacent cell. Mark wall PRESENT.
                    * Similarly for right_flag and right side wall.

                Wall Proximity Thresholding (LL--MAP--1.2.3, LL--RELIAB--1.2.1):
                - Apply configurable numeric thresholds and hysteresis on filtered ultrasonic measurements to reduce noise:
                    * Define threshold_d_wall (distance where wall is assumed).
                    * Use two thresholds for hysteresis: d_on &lt; d_off:
                        - If distance below d_on for M consecutive cycles, set frontWallPresent true.
                        - If distance above d_off for M consecutive cycles, clear frontWallPresent.
                    * N and M are configurable (with recommended default N=3; 2 ≤ N ≤ 10).
                - Hysteresis prevents flip-flopping between wall and free.

                Wall Avoidance Maneuvers (LL--MAP--1.2.4, LL--RELIAB--1.1.1, LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1):
                - For each control loop, evaluate predicted trajectory (based on current motion primitive and speed) against:
                    * Grid-map walls within a corridor around path (with clearance margin M and robot footprint).
                    * Real-time sensor-based wall detections.
                - If predicted trajectory intersects a wall within one cell length (17.2 cm) or clearance margin M (LL--RELIAB--1.1.1):
                    * Determine avoidance maneuver:
                        - If front wall only: STOP and turn left or right depending on surrounding map occupancy and frontiers.
                        - If side wall encroaching: plan arc turn that increases distance to wall while maintaining approximate forward progress if safe.
                    * Issue WD_AvoidanceCommand to Motion Control with suggested type and orientation.

                Emergency Stop (LL--RELIAB--1.1.2, LL--INTERF--1.2.1):
                - Compute nominal stopping distance S at current speed (using speed-to-velocity mapping and deceleration profile).
                - Configure emergency distance threshold D_emg &lt; S accounting for ultrasonic uncertainty interval.
                - If a wall or obstacle is detected within D_emg in forward direction, or strong IR detection indicates immediate side collision:
                    * Immediately assert WD_EmergencyStop.
                    * Motion Control must issue motor_set(0,0) without waiting for state transitions.
                    * Movement does not resume until Motion Control and Mission Control establish a new safe trajectory.

            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Executed every control loop cycle (sensor sampling rate 10–50 Hz, default 20 Hz).
                - Wall detection uses the latest filtered sensor data from the same cycle.
                - Avoidance checks must run before Motion Control issues motor_set for the current cycle to allow last-moment override.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Emergency stop has priority over normal motion or avoidance maneuvers.
                - Wall detection decisions affecting the grid map are only taken when:
                    * sensor readings are valid (not out-of-range),
                    * pose alignment constraints are satisfied (for IR),
                    * and consistency checks confirm stable detection where needed.
                - Avoidance commands never propose trajectories that violate minimum clearance margin M given ideal execution.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Sensor failure (constant invalid readings):
                    * Component refrains from generating wall detections and signals sensor invalid state; Mapping and Motion Control fall back to conservative behavior (slow/stop).
                - Conflicting sensor information:
                    * In case of high disagreement between ultrasonic and IR, rely on safety-first: treat as potential wall and avoid, but marking the map is delayed until consistency checks pass.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.2.1; LL--MAP--1.2.2; LL--MAP--1.2.3; LL--MAP--1.2.4; LL--RELIAB--1.1.1; LL--RELIAB--1.1.2; LL--RELIAB--1.2.1; LL--INTERF--2.3.1; LL--INTERF--3.1.1; LL--INTERF--3.3.1; LL--INTERF--3.4.1; LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--5</ID>
            <Name>Return-to-Start & Second-Run Manager</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Coordinates return-to-start and second-run behaviors integrating planning and motion. It listens to exploration status events and mission control state, invokes return path computation, triggers fastest-path planning for second run, and provides success/failure statuses back to Mission Control.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_ReturnPathReached</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean event to Mission Control once the robot reaches the start cell following the return path without collision or planning failure.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_SecondRunResult</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Enumerated {SUCCESS, FAILURE}, indicating the outcome of the second run based on reaching the goal region collision-free and executing fastest path.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_ReturnToStartInvoke</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Invocation from Mission Control when RETURN_TO_START state entered. Includes start cell coordinate and current pose.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_SecondRunInvoke</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Invocation when SECOND_RUN state is entered after successful return and exploration complete.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--2</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_ReturnPlanRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Request to Planner to compute path from current cell to start cell on current grid map (LL--RUN--1.1.1).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_SecondRunPlanRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Request to compute fastest path from start cell to selected goal region, using cost parameters tuned for fast time (LL--RUN--1.2.2).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_ReturnPath</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Planned path from Planner for return-to-start: list of FREE cells from current cell to start cell, or planning failure indication.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_SecondRunPath</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Fastest path for second run from start to selected goal cell; includes cost and structure.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_PlanningStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Planning result codes: OK, NO_PATH, GOAL_UNREACHABLE, used to determine success/failure reporting.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_ReturnMotionPlan</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Selected return path for execution by Motion Control, flagged as RETURN profile (normal-safe speed, with collision avoidance and replanning).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_SecondRunMotionPlan</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Second-run fastest path for execution, flagged as FAST profile (higher speeds within safety constraints).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_PathExecutionFeedback</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Oversight feedback from Motion Control: reachedGoal, collisionOccurred, emergencyStopTriggered. Used to decide whether return/second run succeeded.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_GoalRegionSelectionRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Request to Mapping/Goal-Selection logic to choose the final 2x2 goal region based on reachability and cost from start.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_SelectedGoalRegion</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Selected goal region per LL--ENV--3.1.2: 2x2 FREE cells that minimize path cost from start; used for second-run planning.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Return to Start (LL--RUN--1.1.1, LL--RUN--1.1.2):
                - When signaled by Mission Control (after EXPLORATION_COMPLETED or EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT):
                    * Query pose for current cell index.
                    * Send RS_ReturnPlanRequest to Planner for path from current cell to start cell using standard cost parameters.
                    * On receipt of RS_ReturnPath:
                        - If planning status OK:
                            · Forward path to Motion Control via RS_ReturnMotionPlan.
                            · Monitor execution feedback:
                                · If start cell reached without collision, raise RS_ReturnPathReached = true.
                                · If path becomes invalid due to map updates (Planner triggers replanning), update Motion Control with new path segments.
                                · If collision/emergency stop prevents progress and replanning also fails, signal failure and direct Mission Control towards COMPLETED with failure cause.
                        - If planning status NO_PATH/GOAL_UNREACHABLE:
                            · Report failure to Mission Control; do not start second run.

                Second Run Initialization (LL--RUN--1.2.1):
                - After Mission Control indicates SECOND_RUN entry and exploration declared complete:
                    * Verify that robot is at start cell and map is complete.
                    * Request candidate 2x2 FREE goal regions from Mapping (LL--ENV--3.1.1).
                    * Request selected goal region that minimizes path cost via Goal Region Selection logic (LL--ENV--3.1.2, LL--PLAN--1.1.1).

                Fastest Path Computation (Second Run) (LL--RUN--1.2.2):
                - With selected goal region and start cell:
                    * Request fastest-path computation from Planner:
                        - Configure traversal cost model to approximate physical travel time during second run (e.g., increased straight speed and tuned turn penalties).
                        - The planner picks target goal cell within region that yields minimal travel time.
                    * Once RS_SecondRunPath with OK status is received:
                        - Submit RS_SecondRunMotionPlan to Motion Control with FAST motion profile.
                        - Monitor RS_PathExecutionFeedback:
                            · If robot reaches any FREE cell in 2x2 goal region without collision, declare success.
                            · Else (collision, emergency stop, or failure to reach goal), declare failure (LL--RUN--1.2.4).

                Second Run Status Reporting (LL--RUN--1.2.5):
                - Provide RS_SecondRunResult back to Mission Control as soon as SECOND_RUN completes (success or failure).
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - All invocations and decisions execute within control loop, but planning may span multiple cycles.
                - Return-to-start must begin immediately after exploration termination; no explicit separate time limit is defined.
                - Second-run planning and execution are not constrained by the 5-minute exploration limit.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Second Run is never initiated before:
                    * Return-to-start has completed successfully, and
                    * Exploration is declared complete, and
                    * Robot is at start cell.
                - During return-to-start and second run, all motion commands still respect collision avoidance and emergency stop requirements.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - No candidate goal region:
                    * If no 2x2 FREE reachable region exists at exploration completion, second run cannot be performed; RS_SecondRunResult is set to FAILURE and Mission Control transitions to COMPLETED.
                - Planning failures for return path or second run path:
                    * Reported as failures to Mission Control; system may remain stopped at safe position.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--RUN--1.1.1; LL--RUN--1.1.2; LL--RUN--1.2.1; LL--RUN--1.2.2; LL--RUN--1.2.3; LL--RUN--1.2.4; LL--RUN--1.2.5; LL--ENV--3.1.1; LL--ENV--3.1.2; LL--PLAN--1.1.2; LL--EVENT--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--6</ID>
            <Name>Initialization Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Performs system startup routines and provides a single INIT_COMPLETED indication when all hardware and software initialization is successful. It also initializes key parameters such as control loop period, map, and configuration values for thresholds and enumerations as required by dependent modules.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>INIT_InitCompletedFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean flag or event set once after initialization routines finish. Mission Control polls or subscribes to this flag to allow transition from IDLE to EXPLORE (LL--INIT--1.1.1).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>INIT_MissionStartPoll</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Implicit query from Mission Control to read the state of INIT_InitCompletedFlag each control loop.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--9</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>INIT_SchedulerConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Initial configuration for control loop frequency and period T (aligned with sensor sampling rate).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>INIT_SchedulerInitStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Confirmation from Scheduler that periodic loop has been configured successfully.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>INIT_MapInitTrigger</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Trigger to Mapping module to perform initial grid map setup, unknown initialization, and start cell designation (LL--MAP--1.3.3, LL--MAP--1.3.4).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>INIT_MapInitDone</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Status confirmation from Mapping module when initial map setup is complete.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - At system power-on:
                    * Initialize hardware interfaces (motors, ultrasonic, IR).
                    * Initialize core software modules (Scheduler, Mapping, Pose, Planner, Mission Control).
                    * Configure control loop period T and sensor sampling rate (default 20 Hz).
                    * Trigger grid map initialization and wait for confirmation.
                    * Initialize configuration parameters (thresholds, hysteresis parameters, N for consistency checks, etc.).
                - When all tasks complete successfully:
                    * Set INIT_InitCompletedFlag = true (or push INIT_COMPLETED event) within main execution context.
                - If initialization fails:
                    * Keep INIT_InitCompletedFlag false; optionally expose error details via external reporting but never transition to EXPLORE.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Initialization runs before periodic control loop begins or in an early phase of system run. The INIT_COMPLETED flag is set once and remains true afterward.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - INIT_COMPLETED flag is written only once per power-on cycle.
                - EXPLORE is never entered while INIT_COMPLETED is false.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Any failure in underlying hardware initialization prevents INIT_COMPLETED from being set; system remains in IDLE.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--INIT--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--7</ID>
            <Name>Motion Control & Collision Avoidance</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Converts high-level paths (sequences of cells) and profiles (exploration, return, fast second run) into concrete motor_set commands. It implements differential-drive-based cell-center motion primitives, speed-rate limiting, and enforcement of safety constraints (maximum speed, minimum clearance, emergency stop execution).
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--2</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathExecutionFeedback</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Execution progress and status for current path: index of last reached cell, whether path completed, and any collision or emergency stops that occurred.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PlannedPath</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Path and ExecutionHints for the currently active mission phase, provided by Planner.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionPhaseComplete</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notification when motion for current mission phase completes (path finished or aborted). Used by Mission Control for state transitions.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionEnable</Name>
                            <Description>
                                High-level enable/disable from Mission Control: when false, Motion Control must command zero speeds only.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExplorePhase</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Motion context {EXPLORATION_MOTION, RETURN_MOTION, SECOND_RUN_MOTION} for selecting appropriate speeds and primitives.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_TrajectoryForAvoidance</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Short-term preview of intended motion: next cells and approximate distances, so Wall Detection can check for trajectory collisions.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_EmergencyStopAck</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Acknowledgement that motor_set(0,0) has been issued in response to WD_EmergencyStop.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_AvoidanceCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                High-level avoidance suggestion from Wall Detection (STOP_AND_TURN / ARC_TURN). Motion Control maps this into specific motor_set sequences.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_EmergencyStop</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Emergency stop event: Motion Control must immediately call motor_set(0,0).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SpeedUsageStats</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Diagnostic information on commanded motor speeds, used to verify compliance with speed limits and rate-limiting requirements.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_FilteredSensors</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Sensor data may influence dynamic speed adjustments (e.g., slow near walls).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--11</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionPrimitiveExec</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Pose-advance hints, such as "move one cell forward" or "rotate 90° left/right," to Pose Estimation to help snap cell transitions.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PoseFeedback</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Pose updates used to detect when a cell center has been reached and to close-loop adjust motor commands.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Motor Command Interface (LL--INTERF--1.2.1):
                - Motion Control is the single component allowed to call motor_set(uint8_t left_speed, uint8_t right_speed).
                - It ensures:
                    * motor_set is invoked at most once per control loop iteration.
                    * Speed values remain within [0, 100].

                Motion Primitives (LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2, LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1):
                - Provides primitives:
                    * moveForwardOneCell: moves from current cell center to adjacent center along current heading.
                    * turnInPlace(angle): ±90° or 180° rotations to align with maze axes.
                    * arcTurns: for smooth second-run path following (if supported).
                - For each primitive:
                    * Use differential-drive kinematics (wheelbase, drive model, and control-loop period T) to determine number of cycles and motor_set sequences to reach the intended displacement and rotation.
                    * Monitor pose through CMP--11; stop primitive when target cell center or heading is reached.

                Speed Rate Limiting (LL--INTERF--1.2.2):
                - Enforce configurable maximum increments ΔL_max, ΔR_max per cycle for left/right speeds:
                    * On each control loop:
                        - Given desired speeds (L_des, R_des), compute:
                            L_cmd = clamp(L_prev - ΔL_max, L_prev + ΔL_max, L_des)
                            R_cmd = clamp(R_prev - ΔR_max, R_prev + ΔR_max, R_des)
                        - Call motor_set(L_cmd, R_cmd).
                        - Store L_prev, R_prev for next cycle.
                - Limits are tuned to avoid abrupt acceleration/deceleration and wheel slippage.

                Speed Limitation for Safety (LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1, LL--RUN--1.2.3):
                - Compute maximum permissible translational speed V_max_safe using:
                    * Configured sensor sampling rate fs.
                    * Emergency-stop threshold D_emg.
                    * Ultrasonic uncertainty interval ±12 cm.
                    * Braking model (max deceleration).
                - For each mission phase:
                    * Exploration: set target speed V_explore ≤ V_max_safe with margin.
                    * Return: similar or slower depending on risk assessment.
                    * Second run: choose V_second_run up to V_max_safe but still limited so emergency stop can be safely executed.
                - Map translational speed to motor_set speeds using calibration curves.

                Emergency Stop Execution (LL--RELIAB--1.1.2):
                - When MC_EmergencyStop received:
                    * Immediately set both motor speeds to 0 via motor_set(0,0).
                    * Override any ongoing primitives.
                    * Set internal state to EMERGENCY_STOPPED; refuse new motion until Mission Control asserts new safe path and WD_EmergencyStop is cleared.

                Trajectory Execution:
                - For each active path (from CMP--2/5):
                    * Maintain index i of current segment.
                    * Use primitives to traverse from cell i to cell i+1:
                        - Plan sequence: turn to align heading if needed, then move forward one cell.
                        - For second-run, may chain multiple cells into straight-line or smooth arcs when possible.
                    * After each segment:
                        - Update Pose Estimation.
                        - Report progress to Planner and Mission Control.
                    * Once final goal cell is reached:
                        - Command motor_set(0,0) (or maintain minimal speed if required) and mark path as completed.

            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Invoked once per control loop cycle to:
                    * Process avoidance and emergency stop commands.
                    * Update motion primitive state machines.
                    * Issue at most one motor_set call.
                - Response to emergency stop:
                    * Must occur in the same cycle emergency event is received.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - While Motion Enable is false, commanded motor speed is always (0,0).
                - The instantaneous translational speed computed from motor_set values never exceeds configured safe maximum.
                - Rate of change of motor_set speeds never exceeds configured per-cycle increments.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Inconsistent path and pose:
                    * If pose deviates significantly from expected path, component can request replanning via Planner and stop motion until new path is available.
                - Persistent emergency stop:
                    * If emergency stop remains asserted across multiple cycles, Motion Control remains in EMERGENCY_STOPPED state, requiring a higher-level reset before moving again.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--INTERF--1.2.1; LL--INTERF--1.2.2; LL--RUN--1.1.2; LL--RUN--1.2.3; LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1; LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2; LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1; LL--RELIAB--1.1.2; LL--RELIAB--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--8</ID>
            <Name>External Reporting & Diagnostics</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Collects mission status, map summaries, and second-run outcome and exposes them to external interfaces (display, logging, telemetry). It does not influence control but provides visibility for users and debugging.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EXT_StatusRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Polling or subscription to Mission Control’s MC_ExternalMissionStatus data.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EXT_MissionSummary</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Data structure with mission phases, times, exploration completion flag, timeout flag, and second run success/failure.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EXT_MapRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Requests for current grid map snapshot for offline analysis or display.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EXT_MapSnapshot</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Compressed or summarized representation of grid map including start cell and goal region.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Periodically or on-event, collects latest mission status and map data and forwards them to external interfaces.
                - May also log emergency stops, planning failures, and other reliability-related events for traceability.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Reporting frequency is decoupled from control loop; can be slower (e.g., 1–5 Hz) but must not block control.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - External Reporting never issues control commands.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Logging/output failure must not affect control; errors are isolated.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--RUN--1.2.5
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--9</ID>
            <Name>Control Loop Scheduler & Time Management</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Implements the periodic control loop that orchestrates sensor acquisition, mapping, mission control, planning, and motion control. It also provides timekeeping services used for sensor sampling and exploration time-limit enforcement.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_SensorSampleTrigger</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Trigger invoked once per control loop iteration to instruct Sensor Abstraction Layer to acquire new sensor readings.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_SensorSampleConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configuration for sensor sampling rate and timing jitter tolerance from reliability and configuration modules.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_MapUpdateTrigger</Name>
                            <Description>
                                After sensor acquisition each cycle, instructs Mapping module to update grid map using latest sensor and pose information.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_MapUpdateAck</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional acknowledgment of completion of map update within cycle.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_MissionUpdateTrigger</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Trigger for Mission Control state machine update in the current cycle.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_ElapsedTime</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Current mission elapsed time and exploration elapsed time (ms) since mission start. Used for time-based decisions and remaining-time estimation.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_MissionUpdateAck</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional acknowledgment that mission state updated.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--2</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_PlanningTrigger</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notifies Planner after Mission Control to (re)compute or validate current paths if required by new state.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_PlanningAck</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional acknowledgment of planning step completion within cycle.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_MotionControlTrigger</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Final step each cycle to allow Motion Control to issue motor_set based on latest decisions.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_MotionControlAck</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Acknowledgment that motor_set has been called at most once for this cycle.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Maintains a periodic timer with configurable period T (10–100 ms), where loop frequency = sensor sampling rate (LL--SCHED--1.1.1, LL--RELIAB--1.2.1).
                - In each cycle:
                    1) Trigger sensor acquisition via CMP--10.
                    2) Trigger grid map update via CMP--3 (including pose estimation).
                    3) Update exploration time and mission elapsed time.
                    4) Trigger Mission Control state machine update.
                    5) Trigger Planner to compute or update paths as required.
                    6) Trigger Motion Control to issue motor_set within allowed constraints.
                - Ensures all steps run sequentially (in a single thread).
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Sensor sampling rate and control loop frequency are identical and configurable within [10, 50] Hz, default 20 Hz.
                - Timing jitter is kept below configured tolerance; scheduler measures actual cycle duration and exposes it to modules needing precise timing (e.g., Pose Estimation and kinematics).
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - At most one iteration of the loop is running at any time (no overlapping cycles).
                - motor_set is called at most once per cycle.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Overrun (cycle takes longer than T):
                    * Scheduler logs overrun; next cycle starts immediately, effectively increasing measured period for that iteration. Time-based modules use actual measured duration, not nominal T.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--SCHED--1.1.1; LL--RELIAB--1.2.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--10</ID>
            <Name>Sensor Abstraction & Filtering</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Wraps raw ultrasonic and infrared hardware APIs, enforces sampling rate and timing requirements, filters sensor noise, checks for invalid readings, and exposes normalized and validated sensor data structures to higher-level modules (wall detection, mapping, mission control).
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--9</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SENS_SampleRateConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configuration of sensor sampling rate in [10, 50] Hz and jitter tolerance, used to align sampling with control loop.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SENS_SampleTrigger</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Per-cycle trigger from Scheduler to acquire new sensor data.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SENS_FilteredDataToWallDetection</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Provides:
                                - ultrasonic: distance_cm, timestamp, validity flag
                                - infrared: left_flag, right_flag, timestamp, validity flag
                                Filtered and validated per LL--RELIAB--1.2.1 and LL--INTERF--1.1.1.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SENS_WallDetectionFeedback</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional feedback on whether sensor patterns appear noisy, used to adapt filter parameters (not mandated by LLRs).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SENS_CombinedMeasurementAvailability</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean or event indicating whether at least one valid combined ultrasonic + IR measurement set has been delivered since startup. Used by Mission Control to decide EXPLORE start condition.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SENS_ExplorationStartQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Polling from Mission Control requesting status on sensor readiness.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Sensor Sampling & Filtering (LL--RELIAB--1.2.1, LL--INTERF--1.1.1):
                - On each Scheduler trigger:
                    * Call ultrasonic_get_distance() once.
                    * Call infrared_get_dsl_status() and infrared_get_dsr_status() once.
                - Perform validity checks (LL--INTERF--1.1.2):
                    * If ultrasonic returns negative or out-of-range/saturation codes, mark as invalid and either ignore or replace with safe default (e.g., max distance or previous valid value).
                    * If IR returns out-of-spec values, treat as invalid and set flags to "no obstacle".
                - Filtering:
                    * Maintain moving window of last K readings (K configurable) for each sensor.
                    * Apply moving average or median filter on ultrasonic distances to reduce random noise.
                    * Optionally apply debouncing on IR flags (require consistent flags for at least one or two samples).
                - Provide normalized structures per cycle:
                    * ultrasonic: {distance_cm_filtered, timestamp, valid}
                    * infrared: {left_flag_filtered, right_flag_filtered, timestamp, validPairFlag}
                - Ensure sampling rate equals control loop rate and jitter remains within specified tolerance by aligning to scheduler ticks.

            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Sampling once per control loop iteration with frequency in [10, 50] Hz, default 20 Hz.
                - Filtering operations are O(K) per sample; choose small K (e.g., 3–5) to fit within cycle time.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Filtered data provided in each cycle is based solely on current and past samples, never future samples.
                - Invalid raw readings never propagate directly to mapping or planning decisions; they are either replaced by safe values or omitted.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Persistent invalid readings:
                    * If ultrasonic/IR repeatedly return invalid, Sensor Abstraction sets valid flags false; higher-level modules fall back to safe behavior (slowing, stopping, avoiding reliance on map changes).
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--INTERF--1.1.1; LL--INTERF--1.1.2; LL--INTERF--2.1.1; LL--INTERF--3.1.1; LL--RELIAB--1.2.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--11</ID>
            <Name>Pose Estimation</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Maintains an estimate of the robot’s current maze cell and discrete heading using differential-drive kinematics and corrects drift based on map-aligned wall observations. Notifies Mapping when the robot crosses from one cell center to adjacent center, ensuring correct association of sensor data with map cells.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_CellTransitionNotification</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notifies Mapping module when pose estimate passes the boundary between two cell centers, including old and new (row, col) indices (LL--POSE--1.1.3).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_MotionPrimitiveInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Motion Control: which primitive is currently executing; used to anticipate cell transitions and heading changes.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_CurrentPose</Name>
                            <Description>
                                The current discrete pose: {row, col, heading (N,E,S,W)}, plus alignment error metrics. Used by Mapping for associating wall updates to correct cells/walls.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_MapFeatures</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Wall positions and cell centers from grid map used for pose correction based on sensor observations.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_AxisAlignmentFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean indicating whether current heading is within threshold of maze axes (≤ 10°). Used by Wall Detection to decide if IR-based side wall detection is valid.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_WallObservationForCorrection</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Wall Detection: wall proximity and alignment cues for pose correction (LL--POSE--1.1.2).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--9</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_IntegrationPeriod</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Measured control loop duration used to integrate kinematics.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_CycleDuration</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Actual time delta between consecutive control loop cycles provided by Scheduler.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Each control loop:
                    * Integrate differential-drive kinematics (LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1) using:
                        - Last commanded motor_set speeds (from Motion Control).
                        - Measured cycle duration Δt.
                        - Wheelbase and conversion factors where needed.
                    * Convert continuous pose (x, y, θ) to cell-level pose:
                        - Determine (row, col) by mapping x,y into grid coordinates using cell dimension 17.2 cm (LL--ENV--1.2.1, LL--POSE--1.1.1).
                        - Determine discrete heading (N,E,S,W) as nearest maze axis.
                    * Detect cell center crossing:
                        - If focus cell changed from previous cycle:
                            · Generate CellCenterEntry notification (oldCell, newCell) to Mapping.
                    * Pose Correction using Map Features (LL--POSE--1.1.2):
                        - When:
                            · Robot near cell center and
                            · Axis alignment is within tolerance
                            · And wall detections consistent with existing map boundaries
                          Then:
                            · Snap heading to nearest axis-aligned direction.
                            · Adjust position to nearest consistent cell center (x,y) while maintaining minimal change from integrated pose.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Updated every control loop with latest cycle duration.
                - Pose corrections are applied in cycles where stable wall observations are available.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - There is always one current cell index (row, col) and heading.
                - Pose is consistent with grid boundaries: robot position remains within the 4x8 maze extents.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Large accumulated drift or inconsistent wall observations:
                    * Pose estimation may not be able to reconcile to a unique cell; system may raise a localization error and slow/stop motion until resolved.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--POSE--1.1.1; LL--POSE--1.1.2; LL--POSE--1.1.3; LL--ENV--1.2.1; LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--12</ID>
            <Name>Exploration Status & Time Limit</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Monitors map completeness and global exploration time limit, and publishes EXPLORATION_COMPLETED and EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT events to drive transitions in Mission Control and Return-to-Start logic.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--9</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EST_ExplorationTimerStart</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Trigger to start counting exploration time when EXPLORE state begins.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EST_ElapsedTime</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Mission elapsed time and exploration elapsed time from Scheduler; used to detect 5-minute limit.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EST_MapCompleteQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Periodic query to Mapping for current mapComplete flag.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EST_MapCompleteFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean indicating whether map is complete (no UNKNOWN cells or walls).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EST_ExplorationCompletedEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event enqueued for Mission Control and Return-to-Start when map becomes complete during EXPLORE state.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EST_ExplorationTimeoutEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event enqueued when exploration elapsed time exceeds global 5-minute limit regardless of map completeness.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EST_ExploreActive</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean from Mission Control to indicate when EXPLORE state is active; used to define when to start/stop exploration timer.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - When EXPLORE becomes active:
                    * Start exploration elapsed time counter.
                - On each control loop cycle during EXPLORE:
                    * Check map completeness:
                        - If mapComplete transitions from false to true and no prior completion event emitted:
                            · Enqueue EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event.
                    * Check global exploration time limit (LL--MAP--1.5.1):
                        - If explorationElapsedTime ≥ 5 minutes (300,000 ms) and no prior timeout event emitted:
                            · Enqueue EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event.
                            · Signal to Mission Control to stop exploration moves.
                - Events are enqueued in a system event queue accessible to Mission Control and Return-to-Start (LL--EVENT--1.1.1).
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Checks performed once per control loop during EXPLORE; time measurement uses real elapsed time from Scheduler.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - At most one EXPLORATION_COMPLETED and one EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event per mission.
                - If both conditions are satisfied in the same cycle, both events can be generated, but higher-level logic prioritizes timeout cause.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - If exploration never starts (EXPLORE not entered), no exploration events are generated.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.3; LL--MAP--1.3.6; LL--MAP--1.5.1; LL--EVENT--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>
    </Components>

    <StateMachines version="1">
        <StateMachine>
            <ID>FSM--1</ID>
            <OfComponent>CMP--1</OfComponent>
            <States>
                <State>
                    <Name>IDLE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Ensure Motion Control is disabled and motors are stopped.
                        - Poll INIT_COMPLETED flag and sensor readiness.
                        - Keep mission status as "not started".
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>EXPLORE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Enable Motion Control with exploration profile.
                        - Request/update frontier set and select exploration targets.
                        - Request paths to selected targets from Planner.
                        - Command motion along planned paths.
                        - Monitor exploration completed/timeout events.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>RETURN_TO_START</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Invoke return-to-start service to compute path to start cell.
                        - Command Motion Control to follow return path.
                        - Monitor arrival at start cell or planning failure.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>SECOND_RUN</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Invoke goal-region selection and fastest-path planner.
                        - Command Motion Control to execute fastest path with fast profile.
                        - Monitor path completion and collision status.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>COMPLETED</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Disable new motion commands (motors stopped except for holding).
                        - Maintain final second-run status and mission summary for external reporting.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
            </States>
            <Transitions>
                <Transition>
                    <From>IDLE</From>
                    <To>EXPLORE</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - INIT_COMPLETED indication received from Initialization Module AND
                        - At least one valid combined ultrasonic + IR measurement has been provided by Sensor Abstraction Layer.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - No fatal initialization errors recorded.
                        - (Optional) External start command, if implemented, is true.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Record mission start time.
                        - Reset exploration elapsed time counter.
                        - Set exploration status to "running".
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>EXPLORE</From>
                    <To>RETURN_TO_START</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Receipt of EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event from Exploration Status module OR
                        - Receipt of EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Current exploration path execution has been stopped or can be safely aborted.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Disable further frontier target selection.
                        - Command Motion Control to stop current exploration motion as soon as safe.
                        - Invoke RETURN_TO_START service in CMP--5 to compute return path.
                        - Record reason for termination (COMPLETED vs TIMEOUT).
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>RETURN_TO_START</From>
                    <To>SECOND_RUN</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Return-to-start module signals RS_ReturnPathReached (robot is at start cell) AND
                        - Exploration had completed (EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event occurred) AND
                        - MapComplete flag is true.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - No planning failures flagged during return path execution.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Set SECOND_RUN status to RUNNING.
                        - Invoke second-run fastest-path computation and execution via CMP--5.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>RETURN_TO_START</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Return-to-start module reports planning failure or inability to reach start cell, OR
                        - Exploration was terminated due to timeout and there is a policy to end mission without second run.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Path replanning attempts have been exhausted or deemed futile.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Record mission failure cause.
                        - Set second-run status to FAILURE.
                        - Disable Motion Control.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>SECOND_RUN</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Second-run module reports RS_SecondRunResult either SUCCESS or FAILURE.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Second-run path execution has stopped and motors are at rest or in hold.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Latch second-run status (SUCCESS or FAILURE).
                        - Record mission end time and full mission summary.
                        - Disable Motion Control for any further commands.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
            </Transitions>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.1; LL--MAP--1.1.2; LL--MAP--1.1.3; LL--RUN--1.1.1; LL--RUN--1.2.1; LL--RUN--1.2.4; LL--RUN--1.2.5; LL--EVENT--1.1.1; LL--INIT--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </StateMachine>

        <StateMachine>
            <ID>FSM--2</ID>
            <OfComponent>CMP--7</OfComponent>
            <States>
                <State>
                    <Name>MC_IDLE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Maintain motor_set(0,0).
                        - Clear any active motion primitives.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>MC_EXECUTING_PATH</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Execute current path segments using motion primitives with appropriate speed profile.
                        - Update pose and report progress.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>MC_EMERGENCY_STOPPED</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Keep motors at speed 0.
                        - Await higher-level clearance to resume movement.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
            </States>
            <Transitions>
                <Transition>
                    <From>MC_IDLE</From>
                    <To>MC_EXECUTING_PATH</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - New valid path is assigned from Planner AND
                        - Motion Enable from Mission Control is true.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - No emergency stop active.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Initialize motion primitive sequence for first path segment.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>MC_EXECUTING_PATH</From>
                    <To>MC_IDLE</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - All segments of current path have been executed AND robot is at goal cell.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - No emergency stop active.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Command motor_set(0,0).
                        - Notify Mission Control and Planner of path completion.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>MC_EXECUTING_PATH</From>
                    <To>MC_EMERGENCY_STOPPED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - EmergencyStop event from Wall Detection is received.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - None; always takes precedence.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Immediately issue motor_set(0,0).
                        - Report emergency stop to Mission Control and Planner.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>MC_EMERGENCY_STOPPED</From>
                    <To>MC_IDLE</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Mission Control provides a new safe trajectory and clears emergency condition.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Motors are stopped.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Reset internal motion primitive state.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
            </Transitions>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--RUN--1.1.2; LL--RUN--1.2.3; LL--INTERF--1.2.1; LL--INTERF--1.2.2; LL--RELIAB--1.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </StateMachine>

        <StateMachine>
            <ID>FSM--3</ID>
            <OfComponent>CMP--12</OfComponent>
            <States>
                <State>
                    <Name>EST_IDLE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Exploration timer stopped.
                        - No events generated.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>EST_RUNNING</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Exploration timer running.
                        - Checking map completeness and timeout each cycle.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>EST_DONE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Exploration events no longer generated.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
            </States>
            <Transitions>
                <Transition>
                    <From>EST_IDLE</From>
                    <To>EST_RUNNING</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - EXPLORE state is entered in Mission Control.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - None.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Reset exploration elapsed time to 0.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>EST_RUNNING</From>
                    <To>EST_DONE</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event generated OR
                        - EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event generated AND Mission Control has transitioned out of EXPLORE.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - None.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Stop exploration timer.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
            </Transitions>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.5.1; LL--EVENT--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </StateMachine>
    </StateMachines>

    <AdditionalData version="1">
        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--1</ID>
            <Content>
                Cell and Wall Enumerations:

                - CellState enumeration for maze cells:
                    enum CellState { UNKNOWN = 0, FREE = 1, BLOCKED = 2 };

                - WallState enumeration for inter-cell walls:
                    enum WallState { WALL_UNKNOWN = 0, PRESENT = 1, ABSENT = 2 };

                Transition rules during a mission:
                - CellState:
                    * UNKNOWN -&gt; FREE
                    * UNKNOWN -&gt; BLOCKED
                - WallState:
                    * WALL_UNKNOWN -&gt; PRESENT
                    * WALL_UNKNOWN -&gt; ABSENT

                No reverse transitions or cross transitions (FREE to BLOCKED, PRESENT to ABSENT, etc.) are permitted within a mission.

            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.3.5; LL--MAP--1.4.1; LL--MAP--1.4.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--2</ID>
            <Content>
                Grid Coordinate and Wall Indexing Scheme:

                - Grid coordinates:
                    * Maze has 4 rows (0..3) and 8 columns (0..7).
                    * Cell at (row, col) corresponds to physical area:
                        x ∈ [col * 17.2 cm, (col + 1) * 17.2 cm)
                        y ∈ [row * 17.2 cm, (row + 1) * 17.2 cm)
                    * Start cell fixed at (0, 0).

                - Wall indexing:
                    * Horizontal walls: between rows r and r+1, for r = 0..4, columns c = 0..7.
                        · horizontalWalls[r][c]:
                            - r = 0 represents walls above row 0.
                            - r = 4 represents walls below row 3.
                    * Vertical walls: between columns c and c+1, for c = 0..8, rows r = 0..3.
                        · verticalWalls[r][c]:
                            - c = 0 represents walls to the left of column 0.
                            - c = 8 represents walls to the right of column 7.

                - Inter-cell wall mapping:
                    * Between cell (r, c) and (r+1, c): horizontalWalls[r+1][c]
                    * Between cell (r, c) and (r, c+1): verticalWalls[r][c+1]

            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.3.1; LL--ENV--1.1.1; LL--ENV--1.4.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--3</ID>
            <Content>
                Cell Geometry, Robot Footprint, and Wall Parameters:

                - Cell dimension:
                    * side length L_cell ≈ 17.2 cm. Used to:
                        - Map linear distances to cell transitions.
                        - Define expected distances from cell center to walls.

                - Robot footprint model:
                    * Robot modeled as circle with radius R_robot = 5.5 cm.
                    * When evaluating collisions and clearance margins, treat robot as occupying any point within this radius.

                - Wall geometry:
                    * Wall thickness T_wall ≈ 1.6 cm.
                    * Walls are centered on cell boundaries; half-thickness extends into adjacent cells.

                - Minimum clearance margin:
                    * Configurable M &gt; 0 cm.
                    * Combined safety distance from robot center to wall:
                        D_safe = R_robot + M + (T_wall / 2).

                - IR sensor:
                    * Effective detection distance ≈ 4 cm from sensor along beam.
                    * Beam mounting angle ≈ 25° relative to robot forward axis.

            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1; LL--ENV--1.2.1; LL--ENV--1.3.1; LL--RELIAB--1.1.1; LL--INTERF--3.3.1; LL--INTERF--3.4.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--4</ID>
            <Content>
                Ultrasonic Uncertainty and Front Wall Distance Computation:

                - Each ultrasonic measurement d (cm) is associated with uncertainty interval:
                    [d_min, d_max] = [d - 12, d + 12].

                - Expected robot-center-to-wall distance interval for front wall in current cell:
                    * Nominal distance D_nominal = (L_cell / 2) - (R_robot + T_wall / 2).
                    * Account for pose errors: ±E_pose.
                    * So [d_exp_min, d_exp_max] = [D_nominal - E_pose, D_nominal + E_pose].

                - Front wall detection rule:
                    * If [d_min, d_max] ∩ [d_exp_min, d_exp_max] ≠ ∅ then:
                        classify front wall PRESENT at front boundary of current cell.
                    * Otherwise, classify ABSENT if repeated non-intersection observed with hysteresis and consistency checks.

                - Collision risk and clearance evaluation:
                    * Use [d_min, d_max] minus D_safe to detect whether projected distance is less than or equal to safe threshold; if so, trigger avoidance/emergency stop.

            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.2.1; LL--INTERF--2.3.1; LL--RELIAB--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--5</ID>
            <Content>
                Time-Aware Planning Parameters:

                - Global exploration time limit:
                    * T_global = 5 minutes = 300,000 ms.

                - Nominal cell traversal duration:
                    * Parameter T_cell_nominal (ms), configurable.
                    * Default value to be calibrated experimentally (e.g., 500–1000 ms).
                    * Shared with:
                        - Time-aware planning heuristics (estimation of travel time to frontiers).
                        - Exploration remaining-time computation.

                - Remaining exploration time:
                    * T_remaining = max(0, T_global - explorationElapsedTime).

                - Frontier feasibility condition:
                    * For each frontier:
                        - Estimate travel time t_travel ≈ pathCostToFrontier * (T_cell_nominal / costPerCellUnit).
                        - Estimate observation time t_obs (e.g., fixed multiple of T_cell_nominal).
                        - Frontier is feasible if t_travel + t_obs ≤ T_remaining.

            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.5.1; LL--MAP--1.5.2; LL--MAP--1.5.3
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--6</ID>
            <Content>
                Path Cost Model for Planner:

                - Base cost components:
                    * c_straight: cost for moving from one FREE cell to an orthogonally adjacent FREE cell without changing heading.
                    * c_turn: additional penalty when a heading change (±90°) is required between segments.

                - Exploration mode:
                    * c_straight_explore = 1.0 (normalized).
                    * c_turn_explore ≥ 0.0 (prefers fewer turns but dominated by coverage).
                    * Edge cost:
                        - For segment with no heading change: cost = c_straight_explore.
                        - With turn: cost = c_straight_explore + c_turn_explore.

                - Second-run mode:
                    * Re-parameterize cost to approximate physical travel time:
                        - c_straight_second ≈ L_cell / V_second_run.
                        - c_turn_second adds time needed for rotation and acceleration/deceleration.
                    * Planner uses these costs to minimize travel time along path.

                - Goal region handling:
                    * For each candidate goal cell in 2x2 region, compute minimal cost path.
                    * Choose goal cell with minimal total cost.

            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--PLAN--1.1.2; LL--PLAN--1.1.3; LL--RUN--1.2.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--7</ID>
            <Content>
                Sensor Data Consistency Check Parameter N:

                - Purpose:
                    * Avoid changing established FREE/ABSENT map classifications based on single contradictory sensor readings.

                - Parameter:
                    * N ∈ [2, 10], integer.
                    * Default N_default = 3.

                - Rule:
                    * To consider changing a classification where map currently stores FREE or ABSENT to indicate wall presence (BLOCKED/PRESENT), require at least N consecutive sensor observations that consistently indicate the contrary.
                    * Due to static map assumption, such transitions are not applied within a mission; instead, the detection is treated as sensor error, and the map remains unchanged, but diagnostic counters can be incremented.

            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--RELIAB--1.2.2; LL--MAP--1.4.3; LL--MAP--1.3.5
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>
    </AdditionalData>
</Design>

